APPARMOR:

AppArmor is a security module of kernel Linux that lets the administatror of a system limit the features of a program.
To declare the restrictions creates for every program a security profile.

It is similar to SELinux, although, it works in a different way.
It restricts the actions that processes can do, for example, a PDF viewfinder only is given access to its mandatory tools for its performance.

Command : SUDO apparmor-status

VIRTUAL MACHINE:

A virtual machine is a software able to load a system inside another operative system.
